main event: A civilian observer spotted a white, possibly blue-tinted, object moving across the sky in Monroe, New York on October 23, 1965.
interesting points: The object was first sighted 40 degrees above the horizon moving northwest to southeast, and disappeared at 30 degrees above the horizon.
The object appeared to flicker just before disappearing.
The observer estimated the object to be about twice as large as an echo satellite.
The object was observed for approximately 1 minute.
No sound, trail, or exhaust was reported from the object.
sighted object: A white, possibly blue-tinted, round object
